ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC TEXTMINE DATA=CAS-libref.data-table < options > ;
    VARIABLES variable ;
    TARGET variable ;
    DOC_ID variable ;
    PARSE < parse-options > ;
    SELECT label-list /<GROUP=group-option > KEEP | IGNORE ;
    SVD < svd-options > ;

The TEXTMINE procedure integrates natural language processing and statistical analysis to analyze largescale
textual data in SAS Viya. PROC TEXTMINE supports a wide range of fundamental text analysis
features, which include tokenizing, stemming, part-of-speech tagging, noun group extraction, default or
customized stop lists and start lists, entity parsing, multiword tokens, synonym lists, term weighting, termby-
document matrix creation, and dimension reduction by term filtering and singular value decomposition
(SVD).

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PARSE < parse-options > ;

The PARSE statement specifies the options for parsing the input documents and creating the term-bydocument
matrix.

Syntax: SVD < svd-options > ;

The SVD statement specifies the options for calculating a truncated singular value decomposition (SVD) of
the large, sparse term-by-document matrix that is created during the parsing phase of PROC TEXTMINE.
